theorem Topology.interior_closure_eq_univ_iff_closure_eq_univ
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (closure A) = (Set.univ : Set X) ↔ closure A = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
  constructor
  · intro hInt
    -- Since `interior (closure A) = univ`, the inclusion
    -- `interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A` yields `univ ⊆ closure A`.
    have h_sub : (Set.univ : Set X) ⊆ closure A := by
      simpa [hInt] using
        (interior_subset : interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A)
    -- The reverse inclusion is trivial, so we obtain equality.
    exact Set.Subset.antisymm (Set.Subset_univ _) h_sub
  · intro hCl
    -- The existing lemma gives the desired implication.
    exact
      Topology.interior_closure_eq_univ_of_dense
        (X := X) (A := A) hCl

theorem Topology.closure_eq_univ_of_closure_interior_eq_univ
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (h : closure (interior A) = (Set.univ : Set X)) :
    closure A = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  ·
    intro x _
    simp
  ·
    have h_sub : closure (interior A) ⊆ closure A :=
      Topology.closure_interior_subset_closure (X := X) (A := A)
    simpa [h] using h_sub

theorem Topology.boundary_empty_iff_isOpen_and_isClosed {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    closure A \ interior A = (∅ : Set X) ↔ (IsOpen A ∧ IsClosed A) := by
  classical
  constructor
  · intro hBoundary
    -- Step 1: show `closure A ⊆ interior A`.
    have h_cl_subset_int : closure A ⊆ interior A := by
      intro x hxCl
      by_contra hxInt
      have : x ∈ closure A \ interior A := ⟨hxCl, hxInt⟩
      have : x ∈ (∅ : Set X) := by
        simpa [hBoundary] using this
      exact this.elim
    -- Step 2: show `interior A ⊆ closure A`.
    have h_int_subset_cl : interior A ⊆ closure A := by
      intro x hxInt
      exact subset_closure (interior_subset hxInt)
    -- Step 3: deduce `interior A = closure A`.
    have h_int_eq_cl : interior A = closure A :=
      Set.Subset.antisymm h_cl_subset_int h_int_subset_cl
    -- Step 4: prove `A = interior A` (and hence `A = closure A`).
    have hA_eq_int : A = interior A := by
      apply Set.Subset.antisymm
      · intro x hxA
        have : x ∈ closure A := subset_closure hxA
        exact h_cl_subset_int this
      · exact interior_subset
    have hA_eq_cl : A = closure A := by
      simpa [hA_eq_int] using h_int_eq_cl
    -- Step 5: obtain openness and closedness of `A`.
    have hOpen : IsOpen A := by
      simpa [hA_eq_int] using isOpen_interior
    have hClosed : IsClosed A := by
      simpa [hA_eq_cl] using isClosed_closure
    exact And.intro hOpen hClosed
  · rintro ⟨hOpen, hClosed⟩
    -- `A` is both open and closed, hence `interior A = A` and `closure A = A`.
    have h_int : interior A = A := hOpen.interior_eq
    have h_cl  : closure A  = A := hClosed.closure_eq
    simpa [h_int, h_cl, Set.diff_self] using rfl

theorem Topology.P3_of_isOpen_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (h : IsOpen (closure A)) : Topology.P3 A := by
  dsimp [Topology.P3]
  intro x hxA
  have hx_closure : (x : X) ∈ closure A := subset_closure hxA
  simpa [h.interior_eq] using hx_closure
